<L>__{interior dining hall, sandringham night}
<A>__{clear soup is being served at the immense table. places set for five, but only bertie and his mother are seated. the clinking of silver and china. finally:}
<C>__{queen mary}
<D>__{i want my jewelry divided equally. elizabeth gets first choice. she's not greedy.}
<C>__{bertie}
<D>__{may i remind you, you're not the one who's dying, mother.}
<C>__{queen mary}
<D>__{where are the others?}
<C>__{bertie}
<D>__{lord wigram and dr dawson are making arrangements.}
<C>__{queen mary}
<D>__{what sort of arrangements?}
<C>__{bertie}
<D>__{they didn't say.}
<C>__{queen mary}
<D>__{and david? fetch him.}
